# zscaler.ziacloud Collection

This repo is an Ansible Collection (`zscaler.ziacloud`) for **Zscaler Internet
Access (ZIA)**, built on top of the `zscaler-sdk-python` SDK. Modules never call
the REST API directly — all calls go through the SDK via `ZIAClientHelper`.

See `CLAUDE.md` at the repo root for the full guide.

## Non-negotiables

- Module files: `plugins/modules/zia_<resource>.py` (CRUD) and
  `zia_<resource>_info.py` (read-only). FQCN `zscaler.ziacloud.zia_<resource>`.
- Every new/changed module **MUST** ship with:
  1. a unit test at `tests/unit/plugins/modules/test_zia_<resource>.py`,
  2. an ignore entry in **every** `tests/sanity/ignore-2.1X.txt`
     (`plugins/modules/zia_<resource>.py validate-modules:missing-gplv3-license`),
  3. passing `black` formatting (`make format` / `make check-format`).
- Keep the version in sync between `galaxy.yml` and
  `plugins/module_utils/version.py`.
- Reuse `plugins/module_utils/utils.py` helpers (`deleteNone`, `normalize_list`,
  `collect_all_items`, validators) and `plugins/doc_fragments/fragments.py`
  documentation fragments instead of duplicating them.

## SDK call contract

```python
client = ZIAClientHelper(module)              # __getattr__ -> client.zia.<service>
result, _unused, error = client.<service>.<method>(...)
if error:
    module.fail_json(msg=f"Error ...: {to_native(error)}")
data = result.as_dict() if hasattr(result, "as_dict") else result
```

When in doubt, copy the structure of the closest existing module
(e.g. `zia_rule_labels.py` for simple CRUD, `zia_cloud_firewall_ips_rules.py`
for rule-style resources).
